title: For Sale/Trade:  Intratec Tec-22 Scorpion (Pre-Ban)
postcontent:
Original Intratec "Tec-22" Scorpion with the pre-1994 AWB threaded barrel (and barrel protector).  This pistol is compatible with ALL Ruger 10/22 magazines and drums.  I bought it several months ago. 

The previous owner reported issues with jamming.  I installed a new Volquartsen extractor and a new firing pin/firing pin spring.  It now functions pretty well with CCI Mini Mags but it's all about the position of the magazine, so the rounds feed into the chamber properly (regardless of the magazine type).  This is a pretty common problem with these guns and I've heard of some folks doing modifications to the magazine well to make sure the magazines seat/feed correctly.  I didn't feel like doing that, as long as the magazine is pushed forward (not pulled backward), it works pretty well.  Occasionally, the top cover works it way lose after several rounds - but you can just pop it back down.  The top cover and barrel have some slight flecks of surface rust.  When this thing is lubed and loaded with good ammo, it is very fun to shoot.

The gun will come with:
- Extra firing pin (x 1)
- Extra firing pin spring (x2)

I will also include one [B]super evil "high capacity" magazine[/B] for a full price deal or an interesting trade.  Seriously, this magazine is PURE evil*...I wouldn't turn my back on it. 

Terms: You must have WA DL.  No paperwork is necessary, if you have WA CPL.  Without CPL, we will complete a simple bill of sale for my records only.  You are welcome to have a copy as well.


* - At least that's what the Mayor of Seattle told me.

title: For Sale:  Pre-Ban AR-15 556 rifle
location: deep woods, SW MS., Mississippi, United States
postcontent:
This one is a win win. Should the anti-legislation die off, you can still get the asking price from a ban state. It was purchased new in 1991 by a Police officer who qualified with it once, and carried it as a patrol rifle for roughly two years before he was told he had to go back to the issued shotgun. He sold to the second in 1993 and estimated a less than 500 rd count. The second owner heavily lubed it and stored it then. It appears to be a good semi-auto copy of a Colt A1-A2. It is one of the first 5000 made by Eagle Arms of Coal Valley, Il. the retail arm of LMT,  owned by Karl Lewis.  It has a  20'' chrome lined barrel and bore, and forged recievers. This company was sold in the wake of the AWB in 1994 by Mr. Lewis to Mark Westeom. who later aquired the Armalite trademark. 
It is not from the Armalite budget line. This rifle was a forerunner of both the Armalite, and LMT ARs. It came from the factory as a complete rifle but it does not have a white stamp on front of the magwell. That practice began under Mr. Westrom. It does not have a cast lower, nor was  the companies inventory sold to DPMS, or DSA.  Those statements may apply to the guns made by Esential Arms of Louisiana.( which may be fine guns, I have no experience with them.However, according to AR-15.com LMT continues to supply receivers to a number of companies. 
 LMT = LMT, Lauer, DS Arms, PWA, Eagle,Armalite, Knights Armament, Barrett, Bushmaster.
Condition would be an easy good-very good. There is some minor fading ( not wear) in spots., that appear a Colt like Greenish Gray.
It comes with 200 rds. 160 redbox, 40 mil surp and new/w tags Black Hawk nylon case. The price is firm as I am helping a friend with an estate liguidation.

title: For Sale:  ARs, SCARs, SKSs, AKs, 10/22s, Glocks - Read this first
postcontent:
ARMSLIST and all other gun marketplaces are community run for the most part. As a gun community we need to come together to rid ourselves of one of the deadliest sins - greed. We are all tired of seeing $500 AK-47s listed at $2000, and $800 fully upgraded AR-15s posted for $4500. Guess what? As gun buyers and members on this and other forums, we are just as responsible for the state of our society as the price gougers and hoarders. We need to come together and do two thing: (1) STOP BUYING AT THESE RIDICULOUS PRICES and (2) click on the ad, go to "Flag" at the top, and press "overpriced." This whole process takes 1.3968 seconds. 

These price criminals only have business if someone is ignorant enough to buy and if they spread their advertisement. NOTE TO GUN COMMUNITY: Guns aren't going anywhere. Ammo isn't going anywhere. Magazines are the biggest threat of changing but let's face it, do we really need 100 round drums or is that more of a want? Every time you skip over a $10,000 ad for a $3000 purchased SCAR 17, you have just became part of the problem. Send them a hate email showing the prices before hoarding and then promptly flag their ad so we can get prices back under the 1000s where they all belong. For the uninformed or misinformed audience, I have put together a short list of reasonable prices for standard guns. What I am asking is that everyone read this post and then immediately copy and paste it to another state's listing in the US. Add your own two cents in if you'd like or if I got anything wrong. The regularity will only return if we make it. 

AR-15: $600-$1300 depending on brand and usage (shots fired, wear, etc..)
AK-47: $400-$900
SKS:$300-$500
SCAR 16/17: $2000/$2800
AR-10: $1000-1500
Glock: $400-600
10/22: $229
ACR: $2000
1911: $600-1100
9mm ammo: $0.25/round is on the higher end
223/5.56: $0.35/round
.308/7.62 NATO: maybe up to $1/round (on high side)
.22: $0.05/round is high

Again, feel free to add your $0.02, make changes, repost, and then get to the flagging of overpriced scams.

title: For Sale:  Regular Pre-Panic Priced SCARs, ACRs, AR-15s, Glocks, AKs, AR-10s!
postcontent:
ARMSLIST and all other gun marketplaces are community run for the most part. As a gun community we need to come together to rid ourselves of one of the deadliest sins - greed. We are all tired of seeing $500 AK-47s listed at $2000, and $800 fully upgraded AR-15s posted for $4500. Guess what? As gun buyers and members on this and other forums, we are just as responsible for the state of our society as the price gougers and hoarders. We need to come together and do two thing: (1) STOP BUYING AT THESE RIDICULOUS PRICES and (2) click on the ad, go to "Flag" at the top, and press "overpriced." This whole process takes 1.3968 seconds.

These price criminals only have business if someone is ignorant enough to buy and if they spread their advertisement. NOTE TO GUN COMMUNITY: Guns aren't going anywhere. Ammo isn't going anywhere. Magazines are the biggest threat of changing but let's face it, do we really need 100 round drums or is that more of a want? Every time you skip over a $10,000 ad for a $3000 purchased SCAR 17, you have just became part of the problem. Send them a hate email showing the prices before hoarding and then promptly flag their ad so we can get prices back under the 1000s where they all belong. For the uninformed or misinformed audience, I have put together a short list of reasonable prices for standard guns. What I am asking is that everyone read this post and then immediately copy and paste it to another state's listing in the US. Add your own two cents in if you'd like or if I got anything wrong. The regularity will only return if we make it.

AR-15: $600-$1300 depending on brand and usage (shots fired, wear, etc..)
AK-47: $400-$900
SKS:$300-$500
SCAR 16/17: $2000/$2800
AR-10: $1000-1500
Glock: $400-600
10/22: $229
ACR: $2000
1911: $600-1100
9mm ammo: $0.25/round is on the higher end
223/5.56: $0.35/round
.308/7.62 NATO: maybe up to $1/round (on high side)
.22: $0.05/round is high

Again, feel free to add your $0.02, make changes, repost, and then get to the flagging of overpriced scams.
